PASTE_YOUR_READ_ONLY_GHCR_TOKEN_HERE
# ── How to use ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Create a READ-ONLY token (once). Either works — always read-only + set an expiry:
#    • Recommended (least privilege): Developer settings → Fine-grained tokens →
#        Repository access: None · Permissions → Packages: Read-only · set an expiry.
#        Test it first:  echo TOKEN | docker login ghcr.io -u joshuakawalya766 --password-stdin
#                        docker pull ghcr.io/joshuakawalya766/dental-dashboard:latest
#    • Reliable fallback: Tokens (classic) → scope ONLY  read:packages  (definitely works).
# 2. Copy this file to  ghcr-token.txt  (drop the .example) and paste the token
#    on the first line (delete these comment lines).
# 3. Include ghcr-token.txt when you hand a clinic the deploy/ folder. The Start
#    launcher logs in with it automatically, then pulls the private image.
#
# The token only allows PULLING your packages — nothing else — and you can revoke
# it anytime from the same GitHub page. Never commit the real ghcr-token.txt.
